    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) in true concours condition. This chassis retains its factory 50:50 weight distribution and remains a benchmark for front-midship balance. The 13B-REW power plant features verified high-compression apex seals and a perfectly synchronized sequential twin-turbocharger system, providing a seamless transition at 4,500 RPM. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed short-throw gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum hose has been replaced with high-temp silicone, and the cooling system has been optimized with an aluminum multi-core radiator to prevent heat soak. Zero chassis flex, original double-wishbone suspension geometry, and pristine paintwork make this a definitive collector's specimen.",
